cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper introduces a novel form of steganography in the domain of machine learning, specifically in the context of training sets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential security implications of this technique, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves classification tasks and the use of classifiers, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes solvers based on nonlinear programming and local search, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
